The host device in this instance has a unique MAC (Media Access Control) address of 8a:00:12:3e:d6:be. They detect and address LAN devices (LAN). The host device requests a website connection from the router (default gateway) using MAC addresses. To establish a connection, the host device makes an ARP request to the router to discover its MAC address. This ARP request is broadcast to all LAN devices, and the router answers with its MAC address, enabling the host device to connect and submit the DNS request. MAC addresses identify and address local area network devices. The host device makes an ARP request to the router to obtain its MAC address before connecting. 